  <h2 id="introduction">Introduction</h2>

  <p>AI-assisted software engineering represents a significant paradigm shift in how developers write, test, and maintain code. This blog explores the evolution of AI tools in the software development ecosystem, from simple code completions to sophisticated agentic assistants that can reason about and modify entire codebases. <d-cite key="rumelhart1986learning"/></p>

  <h2 id="language-server-protocols">Language Server Protocols</h2>

  <p>Language Server Protocols (LSPs) provide the foundation for many modern AI coding tools by standardizing how programming language tooling communicates with code editors and IDEs. This standard interface has enabled the development of sophisticated AI-powered features that work across multiple development environments.</p>

  <figure style="text-align: center; margin: 30px auto;">
